-6="figure-474@12.[369,1200,1099,1807]" captionTargetId-7="figure-479@13.[388,1216,195,903]" captionTargetId-8="figure-80@14.[337,1233,195,1631]" captionTargetId-9="figure-94@15.[322,1283,195,1576]" captionTargetPageId-0="6" captionTargetPageId-1="7" captionTargetPageId-10="16" captionTargetPageId-11="18" captionTargetPageId-12="21" captionTargetPageId-2="9" captionTargetPageId-3="10" captionTargetPageId-4="10" captionTargetPageId-5="11" captionTargetPageId-6="12" captionTargetPageId-7="13" captionTargetPageId-8="14" captionTargetPageId-9="15" captionText-0="Figure 3. Holotype skull of Marzanoptera tersillae in dorsal view.A, left premaxilla. B, right premaxilla. C, photographic representation of the skull. D, anatomical interpretation of the skull. Scale bar: 20 cm." captionText-1="Figure 4. Computed tomography (CT) scan reconstruction of the holotype skull of Marzanoptera tersillae in ventral view. Note that the squamosals are not included because of size limitations for the CT scanning machine. Scale bar: 20 cm." captionText-10="Figure 14. Postcranial skeleton of Marzanoptera tersillae (holotype). A, atlas in anterior view. B, atlas in posterior view. C, axis in anterior view. D, axis in posterior view. E, C3 in anterior view. F, C4 in anterior view. G, C5 in anterior view. H, C6 in anterior view. I, C7 in anterior view. J, T1 in anterior view. Kâ€“M, anterior thoracic vertebrae in anterior view. N, vertebral epiphyses. Scale bars: 20 cm." captionText-11="Figure 15. Postcranial skeleton of Marzanoptera tersillae (holotype). A, B, thoracic vertebrae in ventrolateral view, showing a ventral keel (not to scale; A, same vertebra as shown in K; B, same vertebra as shown in L). C, D, undetermined thoracic vertebra. E, F, additional undetermined thoracic vertebra. G, H, undetermined lumbar vertebra. I, J, undetermined thoracic vertebra. K, ribs in anterior view. Scale bars: 15 cm in Câ€“J; 10 cm in K." captionText-12="Figure 16. Evidence of shark interactions. Ribs of Marzanoptera tersillae (holotype) showing tips of shark teeth embedded into the bone. A, double-headed rib. B, proximal diaphysis of a double-headed rib. C, proximal diaphysis of a possibly double-headed rib. D, diaphysis of a rib. White triangles indicate the shark teeth. Scale bars: 10 cm." captionText-2="Figure 6. Holotype skull of Marzanoptera tersillae in lateral view. A, photographic representation of the skull in right lateral view. B, anatomical interpretation. C, photographic representation of the skull in left lateral view. D, anatomical interpretation. Scale bar: 10 cm." captionText-3="Figure 7. Holotype skull of Marzanoptera tersillae in anterior and posterior views. Note that the squamosals are not included because of size limitations for the computed tomography (CT) scanning machine. A, CT scan-based tridimensional rendering of the skull in anterior view.B, cross-section of the skull at the level of the interorbital region of the frontal, showing the squared outline of the depression medial to the supraorbital processes of the frontal. C, CT scan-based tridimensional rendering of the skull in posterior view. B, photographic representation of the skull in posterior view from a slightly ventral point of view. Scale bar: 30 cm." captionText-4="Figure 8. Vertex of the holotype skull of Marzanoptera tersillae. A, computed tomography scan view of the vertex. B, anatomical interpretation. Scale bar: 30 cm." captionText-5="Figure 9. Temporal fossa of the holotype skull of Marzanoptera tersillae. Note that the squamosals are not included because of size limitations for the computed tomography (CT) scanning machine. A, CT scan-based tridimensional reconstruction of the right temporal fossa and the skull in anterolateral view. B, anatomical interpretation. C, CT scan-based tridimensional reconstruction of the left temporal fossa and the skull in anterolateral view. D, anatomical interpretation. Scale bar: 30 cm." captionText-6="Figure 10. Right posterolateral portion of the holotype skull of Marzanoptera tersillae showing the posterior lacerate foramen and associated anatomical structures based on computed tomography scan reconstruction. Scale bar: 10 cm." captionText-7="Figure 11. Left posterolateral portion of the holotype skull of Marzanoptera tersillae showing the left periotic in articulation with the skull and other associated anatomical structures based on computed tomography scan reconstruction. Scale bar: 10 cm." captionText-8="Figure 12. Left periotic of Marzanoptera tersillae (holotype skull) based on computed tomography scan reconstructions. A, ventral view. B, posterolateral view. C, posterior view. Dâ€“F, details of the pars cochlearis of the left periotic in medial (D) posterior (E) and posteromedial (F) views. Scale bars: 5 cm." captionText-9="Figure 13. Virtual cross-sections of the pars cochlearis of the left periotic of Marzanoptera tersillae showing the path of the facial nerve within the promontorium based on computed tomography scan reconstructions. In Aâ€“D, the arrowheads indicate the positions of the cross-sections of the periotic in ventral view. Eâ€“H, close-up views of the pars cochlearis in medial view. Iâ€“L, anatomical interpretations of images in Eâ€“H. Grey areas represent section areas. Not to scale." pageId="24" pageNumber="1277">FIGS 3â€“16</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
